{
  "stem": "19969.7",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I suppose when you look at the history of the world, religion has been responsible for more deaths than any other single factor in the history of this world.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The Crusades and-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and all professed to be doing the right thing, but they had no hesitancy of killing or condemning somebody who's not of their religion.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "To me, that is a form of insanity.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the Catholics and Protestants even in Ireland, it's-- I suppose that something will go on to the end of time.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I see no signs that the world is getting much more progressive in the-- in the way of religious tolerance or racial tolerance.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Yeah, we're making-- we're getting-- we're making some improvements, but we have a long way to go.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I found a lot of Germans were very contrite about the whole Holocaust experience.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember when-- right after we took Munich, some German I assume had written on one of the public buildings downtown there, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] 'I am ashamed to be a German.' [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] And Bavaria-- the Bavarian people were never really hip on Hitler.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That at one time was an independent kingdom, of course, and a lot of-- Hitler had a lot of opposition in Bavaria and the center of it was Munich.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So you find a lot of-- even today a lot of contrite people, but on the other hand, [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] many who are not.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I was interested-- we met with the City Council of Dachau here in 1989-- '93, when I was over there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We had a chance to meet with the Bavarian-- or the City Council of Dachau.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Now, Dachau is a fairly sizable city, maybe 30,000, 35,000 people, something like that.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
